                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Research words are not sold as default NPC Vendor items. Any vendor can sell research components, spells, dropped weapons/armor, or any other non-default item, provided that another player has sold it to that vendor first.<br /><br />Most default NPC vendor items (aside from certain quest-supplied tradeskill items) have an unlimited supply.  But player-sold items only exist in the quantity originally sold to the vendor.  What you probably saw in Ak'anon was a player-sold Words that somone else bought before you came back.<br /><br />The best places I've found to go vendor mining are near the most popular banks like Shadowhaven, Bazaar, Freeport & Thurgadin.  Also check vendors in non-necro guilds, or in cities without necro guilds (like Shar Val).  <br /><br />One thing you'll notice after a little vendor mining is that NPC vendors can hold more than the 30 or so items shown in the merchant window.  Once you buy something, it's slot gets filled with the next item in the queue.  Sometimes you can get lucky and see something nice (like a rare Words) pop onto the list after buying a player-sold item, exiting, and then re-engaging the merchant window.<br /><br />Also, during a patch (e.g. this coming Wednesday), all NPC vendor lists get reset to default.  So do your shopping beforehand!<br /><br />Good luck, safe travels, and have fun!<br /><br /><br /><br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310159" target="_blank">Gunkk</a><br />52 Iksar Necro<br />The Nameless<br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
